"use strict";(self.webpackChunkmy_website=self.webpackChunkmy_website||[]).push([[5140],{1198:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"/Vision Layer and Reverse Goal Setting","metadata":{"permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Vision Layer and Reverse Goal Setting","editUrl":"https://github.com/imed-ghomari/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Vision Layer and Reverse Goal Setting.md","source":"@site/blog/Vision Layer and Reverse Goal Setting.md","title":"Vision Layer and Reverse Goal Setting","description":"Additions","date":"2025-11-18T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.73,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"date":"2025-11-18T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Refining Social and Spiritual Conduct","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Refining Social and Spiritual Conduct"}},"content":"## Additions\\n\\n* Introduced the \\"Vision\\" layer to the top of the hierarchy to explicitly state the ultimate goal (Janna) that drives all subsequent actions.\\n* Adopted a \\"Reverse Goal Setting\\" framework to better align the system with spiritual aspirations rather than corporate productivity metrics.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n* **System Overhaul**: Transitioned from the OKR (Objectives, Key Results, Initiatives) framework to a Vision-based structure (Vision, Objectives, Domains).\\n    * **Objectives** now refer to the high-level milestones (previously Key Results).\\n    * **Domains** now refer to the specific areas of responsibility (previously Initiatives).\\n* Updated the \\"Getting Started\\" and \\"Obsidian Implementation\\" guides to reflect the new terminology and structure.\\n* Renamed the `Initiatives` folder to `Objective` to match the new hierarchy.\\n* Added link in stinginess domain to the spending process\\n\\n## Deletions\\n\\n* Removed OKR-specific terminology (Key Results, Initiatives) to simplify the mental model and reduce corporate jargon."},{"id":"/Refining Social and Spiritual Conduct","metadata":{"permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Refining Social and Spiritual Conduct","editUrl":"https://github.com/imed-ghomari/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Refining Social and Spiritual Conduct.md","source":"@site/blog/Refining Social and Spiritual Conduct.md","title":"Refining Social and Spiritual Conduct","description":"Additions","date":"2025-08-22T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":1.345,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"date":"2025-08-22T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Vision Layer and Reverse Goal Setting","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Vision Layer and Reverse Goal Setting"},"nextItem":{"title":"Nuances of Sincerity and Reliance","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Nuances of Sincerity and Reliance"}},"content":"## Additions\\n\\n* Included prohibition of joking about religion.\\n* Added mention of death in conversation as a way to remind of mortality.\\n* Included examples in the \\"avoiding false impressions\\" section under \\"sincerity and truthfulness.\\"\\n* Added the last part of the night as a time for repentance.\\n* Added the impact of saying salawat on the Day of Resurrection.\\n* Recognized that there can be situations of differing opinions on important topics where no one is directly involved, and added an action to address that.\\n* Included the prohibition of fantasizing to prevent lusts.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n* Better explained the reason behind \\"false hope of pardon\\" in the \\"Overcoming the Habit of Sin\\" section.\\n* Clarified how to expiate sins in the \\"regret and prevent after committing a sin\\" process.\\n* Slightly clarified the initiative of \\"anger.\\"\\n* Clarified the benefits of repentance.\\n* Emphasized the traveler\'s philosophy in the asceticism initiative.\\n* Highlighted the connection between commanding good verbally and through actions.\\n* Restructured the section on gratitude to differentiate between feeling grateful and actually being grateful.\\n* Renamed the process \\"pride and lesser blessings\\" to \\"don\'t be deluded by fame, wealth, lineage, or beauty\\" to remove ambiguity.\\n* Linked the \\"regret\\" part of repentance to the fear before the sin to clarify when each state should be practiced.\\n\\n## Deletions\\n\\n* Removed the process \\"pride and better blessings\\" and combined it with \\"don\'t consider yourself pious or more pious than anyone\\" because they essentially describe the same action.\\n* Removed the process \u201clower your gaze\u201d and merged it with \u201cguarding your eyes and ears.\u201d"},{"id":"/Nuances of Sincerity and Reliance","metadata":{"permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Nuances of Sincerity and Reliance","editUrl":"https://github.com/imed-ghomari/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Nuances of Sincerity and Reliance.md","source":"@site/blog/Nuances of Sincerity and Reliance.md","title":"Nuances of Sincerity and Reliance","description":"Additions","date":"2025-02-01T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.405,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"date":"2025-02-01T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Refining Social and Spiritual Conduct","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Refining Social and Spiritual Conduct"},"nextItem":{"title":"Taqwa Model and Waiting Logic","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Taqwa Model and Waiting Logic"}},"content":"## Additions\\n\\n* Included a section on hypocrisy in the sincerity initiative.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n* Introduced the concept of minimising waste to the gratitude of limbs section.\\n* Linked the idea of concealing others\' faults to the initiative of commanding good and forbidding evil.\\n* Incorporated the action of not worrying into the reliance initiative.\\n\\n## Deletions\\n\\n* Removed the term \\"self-confidence\\" from the \\"advice to women\\" section in managing the spouse initiative and replaced it with more accurate terminology."},{"id":"/Taqwa Model and Waiting Logic","metadata":{"permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Taqwa Model and Waiting Logic","editUrl":"https://github.com/imed-ghomari/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Taqwa Model and Waiting Logic.md","source":"@site/blog/Taqwa Model and Waiting Logic.md","title":"Taqwa Model and Waiting Logic","description":"Additions","date":"2025-01-02T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":1.65,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"date":"2025-01-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Nuances of Sincerity and Reliance","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Nuances of Sincerity and Reliance"},"nextItem":{"title":"Performance Logic and Process Consolidation","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Performance Logic and Process Consolidation"}},"content":"## Additions\\n\\n* A new, more straightforward method for applying the system was added.\\n* Included the system\'s limitations and how to overcome them in \\"Getting Started.\\"\\n* Another essential process related to properly using blessings was added: \\"Guarding Your Eyes and Ears.\\"\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n* Added more details on how to learn the Quran based on personal experience.\\n* Changed the vault links to include a \\"repeat icon\\" for recurring processes, enhancing visualization.\\n* I added a mention of \\"waiting\\" initiatives and processes, which were overlooked in both scripts in the performance section.\\n* The last section of \\"Choose Your Mentors Well\\" provides additional ways to benefit from predecessors\' stories.\\n* Revised \\"How to Manage Desires of the Private Parts\\" to reflect Ghazali\'s opinion on this topic better.\\n* Renamed the \\"Reciting the Quran\\" initiative to \\"Engaging with the Quran\\" to eliminate confusion with a similarly titled process.\\n* Added links to the Family Support process within the \\"Upholding the Rights of Muslims\\" initiative.\\n* Included a link to the Seeking the Lawful initiative in the Patience initiative regarding acts of disobedience.\\n* Mentioned \\"Inshallah\\" in the Reliance initiative.\\n* Added more details on balancing fear and hope in the \\"Cry and Fear Misguidance\\" process.\\n* Included a link to the \\"Speak Purposefully\\" process through the \\"Managing Differences of Opinion\\" table.\\n* Merged \\"Love\\" and \\"Contentment with Divine Decree\\" into the \\"Love and Contentment\\" initiative since contentment is a sign of love, and they are too closely related to remain separate.\\n* The weekly review section \\"Actions Done All the Time\\" was changed to follow the \\"Hope-Fear-Love\\" Taqwa model.\\n* Updated specific properties in the downloadable vault to align with the merged initiatives and improve the accuracy of the performance graphs.\\n* Highlighted the need to take precautions in the \\"fear of misguidance\\" process, as it constitutes the resulting action of fear.\\n\\n## Deletions\\n\\n* Removed the segment regarding excluding supplication in the \\"reliance\\" initiative to eliminate confusion."},{"id":"/Performance Logic and Process Consolidation","metadata":{"permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Performance Logic and Process Consolidation","editUrl":"https://github.com/imed-ghomari/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Performance Logic and Process Consolidation.md","source":"@site/blog/Performance Logic and Process Consolidation.md","title":"Performance Logic and Process Consolidation","description":"Additions","date":"2024-12-01T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":1.835,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"date":"2024-12-01T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Taqwa Model and Waiting Logic","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Taqwa Model and Waiting Logic"},"nextItem":{"title":"Structural Fixes and Refinements","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Structural Fixes and Refinements"}},"content":"## Additions\\n\\n* Added a new process for supplicating during blessed times.\\n* Added the Arabic version of the dhikr that we should recite at the end of the gathering to the process \\"Speak Purposefully or Maintain Silence.\\"\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n* Merged two processes that discussed praise into one.\\n* Added mention of the review tab in the \\"review initiatives and processes\\" process.\\n* Changed processes tab query to view processes with some initiatives in the waiting stage, hiding them only if all their linked initiatives are waiting.\\n* Updated the performance script to include the edge case of implementing all processes.\\n* Adjusted the performance section\'s first query to correctly count the number of processes needed to reach the next level.\\n* Added more links from initiatives to existing processes to enhance understanding.\\n* Merged \\"minor sins\\" and \\"concealment of sins\\" processes due to their similar themes.\\n* Added more details to the \\"disregard prohibited and doubtful matters\\" process.\\n* Merged \\"being consistent with good deeds\\" with \\"reviewing initiatives and processes\\" as the latter acts as the actionable step for the former.\\n* Linked the last action of truthfulness in \\"sincerity and truthfulness\\" to \\"avoid baseless assumption,\\" as it involves steering clear of questionable situations.\\n* Files with future start dates will appear in the waiting section, even if the waiting property is unchecked.\\n* Performance scripts have been updated to exclude waiting processes and initiatives effectively.\\n\\n## Deletions\\n\\n* Removed the \\"charity in health and youth\\" process and added it to the \\"give happily\\" process as a note.\\n* Removed the \\"situational reactions\\" process as it was too vague; most of its content is included in the \\"accepting accusations\\" process.\\n* Removed the \\"don\'t misuse blessings\\" process because it was too vague. There is already an example of its application linked to the gratitude of the limbs, which is \\"build knowledge in free time.\\"\\n* Removed the process for \\"repenting in the last ten days of Ramadan\\" since it occurs only once a year; an automatic notification is sufficient. A similar action is tahlil in the first ten days of Dhul Hijjah, which also doesn\'t require a process that is due for monthly review."},{"id":"/Structural Fixes and Refinements","metadata":{"permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Structural Fixes and Refinements","editUrl":"https://github.com/imed-ghomari/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Structural Fixes and Refinements.md","source":"@site/blog/Structural Fixes and Refinements.md","title":"Structural Fixes and Refinements","description":"Additions","date":"2024-11-26T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.335,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"date":"2024-11-26T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Performance Logic and Process Consolidation","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Performance Logic and Process Consolidation"},"nextItem":{"title":"Initial Release","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Initial Release"}},"content":"## Additions\\n\\n* Added action details to \\"lower the gaze\\" process\\n* Added performance image example to getting started\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n* Removed some errors and improved writing\\n* Moved \\"Pride and self admiration and humility\\" to bad traits folder, which was wrongfully placed elsewhere\\n\\n## Deletions\\n\\n* Removed mention of baseless assumptions in \\"avoiding harmful speech\\" process documentation because it already has its own process"},{"id":"/Initial Release","metadata":{"permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Initial Release","editUrl":"https://github.com/imed-ghomari/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Initial Release.md","source":"@site/blog/Initial Release.md","title":"Initial Release","description":"Welcome to the first release of Roadmap to Janna. I hope it will be as beneficial for you as it has been for me, or even more.","date":"2024-11-20T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.305,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"date":"2024-11-20T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Structural Fixes and Refinements","permalink":"/roadmap-to-janna/blog/Structural Fixes and Refinements"}},"content":"Welcome to the first release of _Roadmap to Janna_. I hope it will be as beneficial for you as it has been for me, or even more.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nI\'ll aim to release an update at the beginning of each month or less frequently, depending on changes to the system.\\n\\nEach update will include three sections:\\n\\n* Additions\\n* Changes\\n* Deletions"}]}}')}}]);